column5: Hey guys, My Lowrance Hook 5 at the helm was installed about 2 years ago. I have not taken the unit off since installation until last week. When I re- installed the unit ,I cant get any power. I have double checked that the power cable has been connected properly. Any ideas ? Thanks
Broken peg or pegs in the connector plug. Corrosion.
Can you try your unit on different power supply .

Got power at the plug ??? Everyone needs one of these, indispensable trouble shooting trailer lights etc.,  edit: first link was broke  http://www.canadiantire.ca/en/pdp/mastercraft-digital-5-function-multimeter-0520060p.html?cid=KWGoogle_Eclipse_DSA+-+All+Products&gclid=Cj0KEQjwt8rMBRDOqoKWjJfd_LABEiQA2F2biE_JaaH9Av-1o5aO_oMMNljXU3nuF2iuhQbdyOCrouQaAikc8P8HAQ&gclsrc=aw.ds&dclid=CKyC296S2dUCFUqoaQodmbYElQ

I got it figured out. I put the unit in the front to see if it was the unit. Power came on. Traced the wires back to the battery and found a blown fuse and bad connections to the battery. Cleaned the terminals and replaced the fuse. Thanks guys
